  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis damage accumulation model applies the power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger (G-W) correlation, which was derived under the theoretical precondition that red blood cell (RBC) damage accumulates linearly with exposure time and that the stress-damage relationship is stationary across the shear-stress range encountered. This linearity precondition is explicitly required for the scalar damage integral formulation used here.",
